  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Power and Exponential Functions Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Power Functions - Integer Exponents",
    "",
    "**a)** x²: parabola opening up, even function; x³: cubic, odd function, S-shape",
    "",
    "**b)** x⁴: even, steeper than x² near origin; x⁵: odd, steeper than x³",
    "",
    "**c)** Hyperbola, vertical asymptote x=0, horizontal y=0",
    "",
    "**d)** Rational function, vertical asymptote x=0, horizontal y=0",
    "",
    "**e)** Even powers: symmetric about y-axis; odd powers: symmetric about origin",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: Power Functions - Rational Exponents",
    "",
    "**a)** Square root function, domain [0,∞), range [0,∞)",
    "",
    "**b)** Cube root, domain ℝ, range ℝ, odd function",
    "",
    "**c)** For x ≥ 0, combination of linear and square root",
    "",
    "**d)** Hyperbola in first quadrant, vertical asymptote x=0",
    "",
    "**e)** Smaller exponent → steeper near origin, larger → flatter",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Power Functions - Properties",
    "",
    "**a)** Domain: ℝ for n even, ℝ\\{0} for n odd negative, [0,∞) for fractional",
    "",
    "**b)** n > 0: increasing on [0,∞); n < 0: decreasing on (0,∞)",
    "",
    "**c)** Even n: even function; odd n: odd function",
    "",
    "**d)** Vertical asymptotes at x=0 for negative exponents",
    "",
    "**e)** Higher |n| → steeper curves, faster growth/decay",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Exponential Functions - Basic Properties",
    "",
    "**a)** 2^x: increases rapidly; (1/2)^x: decreases to 0",
    "",
    "**b)** 3^x: steeper than 2^x; e^x ≈ 2.718^x, natural exponential",
    "",
    "**c)** a > 1: increases from 0 to ∞; 0 < a < 1: decreases from ∞ to 0",
    "",
    "**d)** Domain: ℝ, Range: (0,∞)",
    "",
    "**e)** y = 0 for a > 1, y = ∞ for 0 < a < 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Exponential Functions - Key Values",
    "",
    "**a)** 1, 2, 1/2, 4, 1/4",
    "",
    "**b)** 1, e, 1/e, e²",
    "",
    "**c)** 1, 10, 0.1, 100",
    "",
    "**d)** 1, 1/2, 2",
    "",
    "**e)** 1, 3, 1/3, 9",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Exponential vs Power Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** 2^x grows much faster than x² for large x",
    "",
    "**b)** When x > n/ln(2) approximately",
    "",
    "**c)** Generally one intersection point in first quadrant",
    "",
    "**d)** Exponential eventually exceeds any polynomial",
    "",
    "**e)** Ratio x^n / a^x → 0 as x → ∞",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: Exponential Equations",
    "",
    "**a)** x log₂8 = 3 → x = 3",
    "",
    "**b)** x log₃27 = 3 → x = 3",
    "",
    "**c)** x = 0",
    "",
    "**d)** x log₂(1/4) = -2 → x = -2",
    "",
    "**e)** x log₁₀10₀₀ = 3 → x = 3",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: Power Equations",
    "",
    "**a)** x = ±3",
    "",
    "**b)** x = 2",
    "",
    "**c)** x = ±2",
    "",
    "**d)** x = 1/2",
    "",
    "**e)** x = 9",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: Exponential Inequalities",
    "",
    "**a)** x log₂8 > 3 → x > 3",
    "",
    "**b)** x log₃27 ≤ 3 → x ≤ 3",
    "",
    "**c)** x < 0",
    "",
    "**d)** x log₂(1/4) ≥ -2 → x ≥ -2",
    "",
    "**e)** x log₁₀10₀₀ > 3 → x > 3",
    "",
    "### Exercise 10: Power Inequalities",
    "",
    "**a)** x < -3 or x > 3",
    "",
    "**b)** x ≤ 2",
    "",
    "**c)** -2 < x < 2",
    "",
    "**d)** 0 < x ≤ 1/2",
    "",
    "**e)** x > 9",
    "",
    "### Exercise 11: Applications - Compound Interest",
    "",
    "**a)** A = 1000(1.05)³ = 1000 × 1.157625 = $1157.63",
    "",
    "**b)** A = 1000e^{0.05×3} = 1000e^{0.15} ≈ 1000 × 1.1618 = $1161.83",
    "",
    "**c)** Continuous gives slightly more interest",
    "",
    "**d)** (1.07)^t = 2 → t ln(1.07) = ln 2 → t = ln 2 / ln 1.07 ≈ 10.24 years",
    "",
    "**e)** EAR = (1 + r/n)^n - 1, approaches e^r - 1 for continuous",
    "",
    "### Exercise 12: Applications - Population Growth",
    "",
    "**a)** k = ln 2 / T, where T is doubling time",
    "",
    "**b)** P(t) = P₀ * 2^{t/T}, exponential with base 2",
    "",
    "**c)** Exponential grows much faster long-term",
    "",
    "**d)** P = P₀e^{0.03×5} = P₀e^{0.15} ≈ P₀ × 1.1618",
    "",
    "**e)** k = ln(P₂/P₁)/(t₂-t₁)",
    "",
    "### Exercise 13: Applications - Radioactive Decay",
    "",
    "**a)** A(t) = A₀e^{-kt}, k = ln 2 / half-life",
    "",
    "**b)** Half-life 5730 years, k = ln 2 / 5730 ≈ 0.000121/year",
    "",
    "**c)** Time when A/A₀ = 0.25, ln(0.25) = -kt → t = ln 4 / k ≈ 3 half-lives",
    "",
    "**d)** Shorter half-life → faster decay",
    "",
    "**e)** Age = (ln(A₀/A))/k, where A is current amount",
    "",
    "### Exercise 14: Power Functions in Physics",
    "",
    "**a)** Inverse square law, force decreases with distance squared",
    "",
    "**b)** Energy proportional to velocity squared",
    "",
    "**c)** Electric field follows inverse square law",
    "",
    "**d)** Sound intensity decreases with distance squared",
    "",
    "**e)** Period proportional to square root of length",
    "",
    "### Exercise 15: Exponential Functions in Science",
    "",
    "**a)** Temperature approaches room temperature exponentially",
    "",
    "**b)** Drug eliminated exponentially from body",
    "",
    "**c)** Learning approaches 100% asymptotically",
    "",
    "**d)** Voltage decays exponentially in RC circuit",
    "",
    "**e)** Population models often include exponential terms"
